english:
  title: Farewell Poem to Shin Cho-gyeong Departing for Yan-du, Composed in the Rhyme of 'Sang'
  author: Jang Hang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I recall the gentleman of Star Mountain—
    integrity in his bearing, loyalty and candor in his words.
    In friendship we bound ourselves as brothers,
    our tastes and aspirations ever aligned.

    One day I came to Cloud Studio,
    called you forth to meet me.
    Observing you closely, my heart stirred with wonder—
    I knew at once you were a man of rare capacity.

    You savored the teachings of the sages,
    and in one bold stride ascended the golden register.
    When at last you came to advise two kings,
    the people rejoiced to have found a worthy minister.

    The imperial court recorded your name,
    marking your appointment with singular honor.
    Official carriages rushed to bid farewell,
    and we raised our cups on the western tower.

    This journey bears the weight of kingdoms—
    yet standing at the crossroads of parting,
    what sorrow remains to lament?
  footnotes:
    - Star Mountain (星山) and Cloud Studio (雲齋) likely refer to places of significance in the lives of the two friends.
    - The 'golden register' (金榜) refers to the civil service examination, the traditional path to official advancement in East Asian governments.
    - The reference to 'two kings' suggests the honoree served under multiple rulers, a mark of distinguished service.
